.TH "gpiochip_irq_domain_activate" 9 "gpiochip_irq_domain_activate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gpiochip_irq_domain_activate \- Lock a GPIO to be used as an IRQ
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gpiochip_irq_domain_activate
.BI "(struct irq_domain *domain "  ","
.BI "struct irq_data *data "  ","
.BI "bool reserve "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "domain" 12
The IRQ domain used by this IRQ chip
.IP "data" 12
Outermost irq_data associated with the IRQ
.IP "reserve" 12
If set, only reserve an interrupt vector instead of assigning one
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is a wrapper that calls \fBgpiochip_lock_as_irq\fP and is to be
used as the activate function for the \fIstruct irq_domain_ops\fP. The host_data
for the IRQ domain must be the \fIstruct gpio_chip\fP.
